      "writtenOn": "2026-07-07T01:18:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The memcpy is unnecessary. Due to the struct being defined as `__attribute__((packed))` the compiler has enough information to perform a direct load despite potential misalignment:\n\n```\nyear \u003d resp-\u003eyear;\n```\n\nHowever, we should avoid all of that: see the comment on line 66 above.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 98,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 100,
        "endChar": 42
      },
      "revId": "2b472ea27be9b3fa5d6aea93711b424b1f0863da",
